PHPIDS plugin for CakePHP 1.3
------------------------------

INSTALLATION
------------------------------
1. Copy phpids plugin folder into your Cakephp plugins folder (app/plugins/)
2. Set up the database table where the intrusion alerts will be stored (Check phpids_intrusions.sql)
2. Configure your PHPIDS settings (phpids/config/phpids.php)
3. Set the base path in PHPIDS configuration file (phpids/vendors/phpids/IDS/Config/Config.ini.php)
4. To improve performance, lets only invoke PHPIDS where we are dealing with user input. Add 

$this->requestAction("/phpids/phpids_intrusions/detect");

to the actions you wish the IDS to monitor

INSTALLATION in CakePHP 1.2
-----------------------------
1. Follow steps described above.
1. Move the configuration file (phpids/config/phpids.php) to the main configuration folder (app/config)
2. In phpids_intrusions.php replace 

  Configure::load('phpids.phpids');


with

 Configure::load('phpids');

PHPIDS DOCUMENTATION
------------------------------
Visit: PHPIDS [http://www.phpids.org]



